rejectedLogRecords.description: The number of rejected log records. A `rejected_<signal>` field holding a `0` value indicates that the request was fully accepted.

errorMessage.description: A developer-facing human-readable message in English. It should be used either to explain why the server rejected parts of the data during a partial success or to convey warnings/suggestions during a full success. The message should offer guidance on how users can address such issues. error_message is an optional field. An error_message with an empty value is equivalent to it not being set.
